Don't joke Mark. That happened to me. I brought in my beautiful CUSTOM BUILT state of the art gaming computer for a VIRUS. My dad, trying to be helpful, calls them up to check on the computer and they say the motherboard needs to be replaced. Now, by now, I had already decided that the moment I got it back they were never touching it again. but my dad, who pretends to be genial and thinks he can make everyone like him tells them to go ahead and replace it (I try not to get mad at my parents but boy did I give him a talking to...okay a yelling to). I FINALLY get it back. It has a USED power supply/source, a YELLOW substandard motherboard AND when i turn it on...graphics card doesn't work.

SOME IMPORTANT TIPS FOR YOU JACK

- To make a functional ship you need to craft an atlas sky core and place it on the ship to make it float, you need to place sails on it to go forward (you unlock the skill to craft engines later on) and you need to place a helm on it to steer, ascend and descend.
- Try not to shoot at people for no reason. It's considered a pretty large dick move in this game and people will tend to hunt you down
- Just scan everything to gain knowledge. Knowledge is used to level up your crafting skills for better ship parts such as engines.
- It's an unwritten rule to ask permission to board another players ship. If people get surprised by you boarding they may think you are a pirate and kill you. (Yes, piracy is a thing in this game)
- Very important When you built a ship, place a personal reviver on it and register yourself to it by holding E. If you die you will respawn on your ship and not on a random island.
- When you open your inventory you have a smaller inventory space below your main inventory called "belt separator". Every item you place there keeps saved upon death. Place your gun and ammo there so you don't lose it everytime you die.

Hope this was helpfull :3

Just remember,  Color code can save lives.

Tip : If someone is behind you at night while you're driving a car, they start to keep their distance and suddenly they turn their lights off, that means they're most likely trying to follow you. The following is an excerpt from the Royal Proclamation of 1763 that deals specifically with Aboriginal peoples:

And whereas it is just and reasonable, and essential to our Interest, and the Security of our Colonies, that the several Nations or Tribes of Indians with whom We are connected, and who live under our Protection, should not be molested or disturbed in the Possession of such Parts of Our Dominions and Territories as, not having been ceded to or purchased by Us, are reserved to them, or any of them, as their Hunting Grounds -- We do therefore, with the Advice of our Privy Council, declare it to be our Royal Will and Pleasure, that no Governor or Commander in Chief in any of our Colonies of Quebec, East Florida. or West Florida, do presume, upon any Pretence whatever, to grant Warrants of Survey, or pass any Patents for Lands beyond the Bounds of their respective Governments. as described in their Commissions: as also that no Governor or Commander in Chief in any of our other Colonies or Plantations in America do presume for the present, and until our further Pleasure be known, to grant Warrants of Survey, or pass Patents for any Lands beyond the Heads or Sources of any of the Rivers which fall into the Atlantic Ocean from the West and North West, or upon any Lands whatever, which, not having been ceded to or purchased by Us as aforesaid, are reserved to the said Indians, or any of them.

And We do further declare it to be Our Royal Will and Pleasure, for the present as aforesaid, to reserve under our Sovereignty, Protection, and Dominion, for the use of the said Indians, all the Lands and Territories not included within the Limits of Our said Three new Governments, or within the Limits of the Territory granted to the Hudson's Bay Company, as also all the Lands and Territories lying to the Westward of the Sources of the Rivers which fall into the Sea from the West and North West as aforesaid.

And We do hereby strictly forbid, on Pain of our Displeasure, all our loving Subjects from making any Purchases or Settlements whatever, or taking Possession of any of the Lands above reserved, without our especial leave and Licence for that Purpose first obtained.

And We do further strictly enjoin and require all Persons whatever who have either wilfully or inadvertently seated themselves upon any Lands within the Countries above described. or upon any other Lands which, not having been ceded to or purchased by Us, are still reserved to the said Indians as aforesaid, forthwith to remove themselves from such Settlements.

And whereas great Frauds and Abuses have been committed in purchasing Lands of the Indians, to the great Prejudice of our Interests. and to the great Dissatisfaction of the said Indians: In order, therefore, to prevent such Irregularities for the future, and to the end that the Indians may be convinced of our Justice and determined Resolution to remove all reasonable Cause of Discontent, We do, with the Advice of our Privy Council strictly enjoin and require, that no private Person do presume to make any purchase from the said Indians of any Lands reserved to the said Indians, within those parts of our Colonies where We have thought proper to allow Settlement: but that, if at any Time any of the Said Indians should be inclined to dispose of the said Lands, the same shall be Purchased only for Us, in our Name, at some public Meeting or Assembly of the said Indians, to be held for that Purpose by the Governor or Commander in Chief of our Colony respectively within which they shall lie: and in case they shall lie within the limits of any Proprietary Government, they shall be purchased only for the Use and in the name of such Proprietaries, conformable to such Directions and Instructions as We or they shall think proper to give for that Purpose: And we do, by the Advice of our Privy Council, declare and enjoin, that the Trade with the said Indians shall be free and open to all our Subjects whatever, provided that every Person who may incline to Trade with the said Indians do take out a Licence for carrying on such Trade from the Governor or Commander in Chief of any of our Colonies respectively where such Person shall reside, and also give Security to observe such Regulations as We shall at any Time think fit, by ourselves or by our Commissaries to be appointed for this Purpose, to direct and appoint for the Benefit of the said Trade:

And we do hereby authorize, enjoin, and require the Governors and Commanders in Chief of all our Colonies respectively, as well those under Our immediate Government as those under the Government and Direction of Proprietaries, to grant such Licences without Fee or Reward, taking especial Care to insert therein a Condition, that such Licence shall be void, and the Security forfeited in case the Person to whom the same is granted shall refuse or neglect to observe such Regulations as We shall think proper to prescribe as aforesaid.

And we do further expressly conjoin and require all Officers whatever, as well Military as those Employed in the Management and Direction of Indian Affairs, within the Territories reserved as aforesaid for the use of the said Indians, to seize and apprehend all Persons whatever, who standing charged with Treason, Misprisions of Treason, Murders, or other Felonies or Misdemeanors, shall fly from Justice and take Refuge in the said Territory, and to send them under a proper guard to the Colony where the Crime was committed, of which they stand accused, in order to take their Trial for the same.

I still remember watching this when it kept coming up in my recommended. It was the first time I had rewatched Minecraft after several years. I also remember thinking that Dream was being rude, and I also watched the video where he was a parrot afterward. At that point, my mind was already made up that Dream was being a jerk to George, but as I watched more, I realized that I actually liked watching these kinds of videos. So, over a year later, I still watch them and a huge fan of the SMP and all the amazing people in the community (of course, not the toxic side). I'm so happy that I actually stayed though, 2021 has been one of the happiest years of my life. All of these laughs and new content never fail to make me smile. Getting my first merch from Bad's shop, watching streams back-to-back while late at night, and showing some of the members to my sisters and them enjoying them, and noticing people at my new school wearing some merch has made me so happy. I honestly can't thank you enough with this video, George :) I can't believe that it's been so long in such a short amount of time :,)

Using evade will extend the time for your combo and give you time to plan your next attack. You get one normal evade before you need to do something else, but you can evade over an enemy as many times as you want and keep the combo going potentially forever.

If you can master it, the blade dodge takedown is an extremely powerful tool in your arsenal. Unlike most other takedowns, it is extremely fast and won't leave you open to counterattacks; it also doesn't require a combo to use. If you are having trouble with it, head to the batcave and fire up the training chamber for a few rounds. I could never get the hang of it in city, but in origins I find myself actually hoping for enemies to pick up knives so I can knock them out faster.

Also I love that in a few scenes, you see Batman's classic white eyes for just a few seconds. Like when you're hanging that one guy with the Christmas hat from the roof of the clock tower. And when you're going up in the elevator, you see it for a split second when the doors open, right before Batman disarms Gordon

I highly recommend going to the training console in the Batcave and picking the combat training option. It has a bunch of tutorials and gives descriptions on how to perform the fundamentals of Arkham combat.

The original GoW gave us solid gameplay, good graphics (for the time), and an epic (if straightforward) story. The sequel didn't make any major changes to the formula, but it gave us expanded gameplay, better graphics, more enemy variety, a lot more unique boss fights, and an even crazier story. I'm hoping we see the same progression with Ragnarok and it looks like most of that is already true: the environments have more detail, we'll be going to all nine realms, we know they've added elemental attacks and different shield abilities, the chainswing is back, looks like there are a lot of new enemies as well. We'll have to wait to see whether the story works, but there are several new characters to introduce and a bunch of loose ends to tie off so they won't be short on ideas.

Remember the Assassins aren't always the good guys. Altair's Brotherhood was riddled with flaws and they basically were Templars themselves (hence why Altair's 9 targets all made the comparisons) and Achilles said in AC3 that he failed the Brotherhood and said to Connor "in your haste to save the world, don't destroy it" which was basically referencing this game. The Templars are still the overall bad guys but sometimes the Assassins can so far the Templars opposition makes them look like the good guys, made more understandable by the fact that some of them actually do believe themselves the good guys.

By this stage you've seen Liam keeping tight lipped around Shay for simply trivial questions, the French Assassin basically having the mentality of a Templar and Hope blindly defending Achilles against Shay's accusations without question. Achilles even risked destroying the entire Homestead and killing everyone on it by having Chevalier open fire on it just to stop Shay when even Ezio risked surrendering the Masyaf keys for Sofia (you can even hear an Assassin in the background saying "Has Chevalier gone mad? He'll destroy the Homestead!").

But as you noted Monro and Gist actually give Shay more detailed answers to his questions than the Assassins did because that's what planted the seed of doubt within Shay's head, so if they'd been more open things might've been different. Also good observation you made about Liam having anxiety and not wanting to question Achilles but that was the flaw with Altair's Brotherhood and why Ezio's was more effective. Overall the Assassins in this game treat the brotherhood like a cult they obey without question because it saved them from the streets but have no value for its principles and Achilles authoritarian outlook only encourages this.

You seemed a bit confused, so I will clarify. You might've figured it out, but just to make sure. When Kratos saved Sindri from the dragon, he gave Atreus the gift of mistletoe arrows, shortly there after (before they meet Mimir) Kratos noticed that Atreus' quiver strap was broken, so he repaired it with one of the mistletoe arrow tips, the next time that Kratos and Atreus went to Freya's house she noticed the mistletoe arrows Atreus was carrying and demanded that we give them to her, she destroyed them and demanded that if we ever came across more that they would destroy them. The reason is that she knows that is the only thing that can break Baldur's curse. Freya didn't notice the arrow tip that was used to repair Atreus' quiver strap though. So when Baldur punched Atreus, the arrow tip was driven through his hand and made him vulnerable.

After the full credits, the game comes back and Atreus has a conversation about the dream he just had. That fimbulwinter was ending and Thor came to the house. Kratos reassures him that it was only a dream, but Atreus tells him that it didn't feel like a dream, it felt real. It felt like...the future. That secret ending is a prophecy that Atreus just had. Now that he knows he is a Giant, Atreus is starting to unlock that power.

One of those small detail things again. But when Kratos jumps off the chisel with Baldur, if you look at Kratos he looks behind himself to see how far of a fall it is, then he gives Atreus a nod and look over his own shoulder again to signal to the boy that he is jumping and wants Atreus to follow. Plus no hesitation out of Atreus there either. They're working together so well at this point.

Just that small moment shows the character growth of both Kratos and Atreus. Earlier in the game Atreus was unsure of himself and Kratos was a tad over protective. Now they completely trust themselves and each other to the point where they don't even need to say a word to know what to do.
Just know the temple holds all the realms in one place including its mass, so Kratos just flipped 9 infinite universes with little effort

I highly recommend to play the first games so you get to know kratos well,
All of them have epic boss fights, epic battles and lots of cool scenes, I saw the video that you reacted to kratos story but give the games a try! I'm sure that you gonna love them.

Fun little detail you should know about the classic games is Doom 1 and 2 took place in 2022 over 130 years before the events of Doom 2016 and Eternal. You played as a Marine of the United States military more retro Military look with combat armour instead of the power armour we see in the more modern games. He was sent to a UAC mars base because he didnâ€™t listen to his officer when ordered to fire on civilians (Unknown Earth Conflict) when the UAC bases were attacked by demons basically first contact with humanity. Doom 1 midway through the demons attacked Earth and in Doom 2 â€œHell on Earthâ€ you fight in cityâ€™s on Earth for the first time. This attack wasnâ€™t as impactful as the one we see in Doom Eternal but was just like any other conflict instead of enemy human soldiers there was demons. This could be the reason for Earth forming under a United Earth most nations wouldâ€™ve fallen. The formation of the ARC is very interesting as they were formed to combat demons so this couldâ€™ve been created after humanity saw what the demons could actually achieve. At the end of Doom 64 which take place after Doom 2 the marine stays in Hell to fight the demons so the big question us old school fans have is how does the new Doom games link to the classic ones (a lot of us thought Doom 2016 was just a reboot having nothing to do with the other games) and my theory is Time moves slower in hell as itâ€™s a different dimension. The Armour The Slayer wears  in Doom 2016 isnâ€™t his Original Combat Armour and from the look of the armour and how the scientists in Doom 2016 spoke about it shows thatâ€™s itâ€™s not from Earth. The Doom Slayer as heâ€™s known now has history with the Night Sentinel a people from a different planet far from our part of the galaxy so thereâ€™s so much story missing between Doom 64 and Doom 2016 which this game will hopefully answer. Cannot wait to see how you find this game.

Which is why 9S is so adamant that it isn't true. He doesn't want to kill 2B, even though he knows that she has killed him so many times.

So as you noticed - towards the end of japanese version of the credits song the singer's voice changes and she seems to be crying, well that's because she is... The lyrics in japanese version are quiet different compared to the english one and it always makes the singer so sad she cries so they decided to keep this version in the actual game, even at live performances, no matter how many times she sings it she always tears up towards the end.

You can listen to the song here - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gEgL-3gfexo
If you play from 4:16 till the end you can clearly hear how her voice breaks down more and more. (Just in case tho don't read the comments, you'll always find some spoilers there).

I'm very confused by people feeling the need to defend Bose and his actions. He clearly abused Jimmy in some way shape or form. You don't take off your tie and wrap it around your hand as you're talking to someone you've locked in a hotel room with you "to talk". He at the very least physically abused him. But given that it sounds like Jimmy was at least a young man by that point, to me it seems more likely it was something else. Given Jimmy is a strong, able bodied, already violent young man, and loud and dramatic to boot, I don't see him cooperating too much with an older out of shape man who he's already afraid of and aggressive toward beating him with advanced warning like that. He very much seems like he'd scream and fight back, which would make what was going on pretty noticeable to everyone in the hotel and probably leave Bose with at least some bruises of his own. It seems more likely to me that some kind of intimidation/abuse that Jimmy didn't know how to deal with caught him off guard and unable to defend himself. Especially considering what Bose said and the way he said it.
The scrapbook could've been Jimmy trying to figure out what'd been done to him, or something he was driven to make out of worry that Bose might hurt him, or something he made prior to meeting Bose as some manifestation of fears he already had about doctors as young man realizing/thinking he was mentally ill, and hearing horror stories about how awful institutions were.
Even if Bose didn't sexually abuse him, I can understand Jimmy making that up, out of fear people wouldn't take Bose beating him seriously. Jimmy shouldn't have to put up with being physically abused either, and if lying about what exactly happened was the only way he felt he could get justice and be safe, I can't really blame him. Bose has no excuse putting his hands on a patient he should have had committed for inpatient treatment the moment he realized he was a danger to others. There is no "What Jimmy did drove him to extremes", there is no excuse for a doctor abusing a patient he's there to help. Beating a patient does them no good, and a doctor would damn well know that.
But the thing is, Bose's actions pretty well indicate this probably isn't the case. Cops are much more likely to trust a doctor with no prior record of abuse than a violent mentally ill young man with probably several complaints and accusations against him. Even substantiated accusations of beating Jimmy, Bose probably could've gotten ignored by police by detailing the things Jimmy had done. Accusations of sexual abuse with no proof and the squeaky clean doctor saying "No, this kid has made false accusations against me before, he's fed me glass, he kills animals, he played a part in the death of a young girl, he's deranged, he needs to be committed." would be ignored by police faster than you could sneeze at, whether or not they were true. And Bose would know that, he would very well know his career isn't instantly over, and he wouldn't be THAT afraid of police involvement. That pretty strongly indicates Jimmy and Rose went to the police with some kind of proof (sheets, clothes, a r@pe kit, corroborating bruises or marks, etc).
Soooooo, Bose is almost certainly a creep and probably a molester, in my opinion...

~ TIPS ON THE EXOTIC BIRDS MOD ~

for the unidentified egg, you will need to put it in a egg sorter (needs to be crafted) and then put the egg it, there is a chance you with either get an egg or eggshells. you can also combine a bird's egg (ex: pigeon egg, magpie egg, etc) with blaze powder to increase the chances of spawning by 20%.

if you kill a peacock and get it's feather and put it in the crafting table with a book, u can make a book of birds which tells you all the birds in the mod. It starts off blank, so you will need to find the birds and left click them with the book to log them. This will reward you with xp.

for the phoenix bird, they can only be hatched with a light level of 9, 10, or 11. you can craft a phoenix egg by surrounding phoenix dust around a regular egg in the crafting table. phoenix dust are rarely found in abandoned mineshaft chests and extremely rare in bird nests. adult phoenixes can be saddled and flown (look up to fly up and look down to fly down) when a phoenix dies, it drops another phoenix egg so you can rebirth another one.

magpies will occasionally 'scavenge' and hold something in their mouth. You can retrieve this item by hitting them, but it will take a while for them to scavenge again, or be more kind and 'swap' the item using wheat seeds.

owls will fly away if attacked. Their eyes glow in the dark.

parrots can be found in jungles. They can be tamed using wheat seeds and will follow you like wolves. You can also make them sit, walk or fly by right clicking them.

roadrunners you need to be holding wheat seeds to catch it's attention

that's all, thx and love you stacy!!

Dear past self:

There is so much more of the world to experience outside your tiny bubble - things to see, music to hear, people to meet, and knowledge to learn. Explore it, but don't latch on too tightly to things, habits, and people that hurt you. Keep an open mind, but stay true to who you are - your instincts won't steer you wrong.Â 

Life will take you to all sorts of places, but you will make friends with people of all walks of life, even if you feel like an outsider at first. Don't look at disdain at those who don't fit the norm, because you will become one of them yourself. In fact, you will start to look at outsiders and misfits as your people, even though you will still find it easy to fit in with influential people who you thought of once as "grown-ups" rather than contemporaries who just happen to be older than you.Â 

Fall in love slowly, not all at once, and with people as they are, not how you imagine them to be like. You will meet someone who will give you a rollercoaster ride of highs and lows. Love her, but don't let your experience with her overpower you or destroy who you are, and learn when to step away when things get rough. Things won't work out between you two in the end, but that spark that brought you together will make you inseparable friends.Â 

Life is a struggle and you may become cynical and jaded, but summon the courage to give your aspirations and dreams your best shot. You may be pleasantly surprised and have fewer regrets later, and whatever happens, even if it seems like the end of the world, you will get through knowing that you tried.Â 

And to my future self:Â 

I hope everything works out for you in the end. I'm sorry for continuously putting off work and forcing you to hurry and rush through everything, but I know you will understand. I wonder where you are, who you're with, what you're doing, and what you're interested in, but I'm sure they are similar to how they are for me now. Have you written that story I've wanted to write? I wonder what you would say to my present self, once I become my past self. I hope they are good things.Â

This is a great video and it's a great idea, but I'm curious: I don't know what events that you're speaking of, but it definitely sounds as though you're giving advice to your old self on how to be happier as a person, on how to get through the events that obviously have happened in your life, basically how to get to where you are now but without as much of a hard time.

But did you consider giving the advice that would help your past self to avoid or change their future, to not "get let down" by other people? It's a question ultimately about regrets, and if you're genuinely happy about where you are in life (and I believe you probably are) then it totally makes sense to advise yourself in this way.

But if you do have regrets, and you're not happy as you are, then do you think it would be worthwhile to advise your past self on how to deal with the events differently, and to turn your regrets around? Or do you think that we learn from that which we regret, and are stronger by accepting our mistakes than we would be if we could go back in time and erase them?

Hey Dodger, here's some Japanese pronunciation tips. The rules are actually really easy to learn. English might tend toward iambic accents, but in Japanese, the first syllable is usually the one with emphasis, and is also usually higher pitched. Also, it saves a lot of trouble to just pronounce r's as l's. Another thing, the syllables in English tend to flow into each other, but the syllables in Japanese are short and well-compartmentalized.

A lot of middle class folks in UK have two accents, a 'home' accent and a 'professional' accent. The former is used with family and friends and is often very regional while the other is used for work, and people often flip between them as appropriate subconsciously. Like I generally speak with a 'Prince Charles' accent (received English) at work or when I meet someone knew, a strong Welsh valleys accent around people from there (that's where I went to school) and a kinda' lazy combination of the two around family (my mother speaks with received English all the time, my dad is Welsh) and my less strongly accented friends. I find it way easier to deliberately start the Welsh accent than to start doing the received English from the Welsh accent.

TBH Sqaishey, you are totally minecraft noob. You need more experience in the new 1.8 update and even about the things before that.

-You can get nametags to name your seperate dogs and animals. But you can only name a villager as a 'baby.'
--You click on an adult villager with a spawn egg and comes out a baby one. You can't name an adult villager because it opens up the trading menu.Â 
-Middle click the scrolly thing on your mouse while pointing at an object. Whatever block you were looking at will be duplicated in your item bar. Only in creative mode.Â 
--You can also middle click when your cursor is over an item in a chest or inventory and you will duplicate it. You can continuously create more banners
-You can't put rose bushes, lilacs, & peonies in flower pots because they are the tall, huge flowers that take up 2 blocks (tall). Although there are similar, smaller flowers such as poppies that you can put into flower pots.Â 
-You can get colored banners and decorate them in a crafting table. The different designs include crosses, straight lines, circles, etc. And you can overlap basic designs to create one huge one, such as a Sqaishey Banner.
-Sea Lanterns are a good alternative to glowstone. They just look better (personally) and they give off the sound of the ocean when you get close to them. They are found in sea temples.
-It doesn't seem like people can actually open chests in other people's plots, at least not in this server. When you said that somebody took one of the banners, that somebody was yourself
-Even if people could open chests, an ender chest is exclusive to each person so nobody can get your stuff and they will end up accessing their own things they have once put in an enderchest at one point on the server.
- Acacia wood is pronounced 'A-kay-shia' not 'A-kak-ia or 'a-cha-chia'
-Stairs automatically 'turn' to merge with a stair next to it facing a different orientation. Try it. Place a stair one direction, and place another stair next to it in a different direction and notice how they merge. But do not place the stair facing the opposite direction. It won't work if you do that. This stair turning is useful for creating roofing and the illusion of a sofa. There is no need to put signs as hand-rests.Â 
-Put glow stone or sea lanterns underneath water, behind stairs, leaves, under carpets, behind paintings and banners as well as under chests. Gives off hidden lightingÂ 
-You can rename items in an anvil
-You can use an enchanted book to enchant armour, weapons and tools with a chosen and specific enchantment type.Â 
-The use of colored glass can do wonders, Sqaishey!Â 
-You can tame bunnies using carrots. They act the same way as ocelots. Once they are tames, they cannot be made to sit down. Nothing with they're appearance changes.Â 
-Use a normal chest instead of a trapped chest. The server allows people to steal from and open chests on other people's plot. The difference is...there is none! It's just that you can place chests and trap chests directly next to each other without them merging. You know how you cannot put a chest block next to a double chest? You can put a trap chest next to it and it has the same functionality. Â

Helpful tips for this game ahead! Woo! (Double post from your previous video, sorry!)

You can use the Pepper Grinder to shoot enemies at long range! Use it against the bolterfly hives/hard to reach enemies (it's also just a generally good weapon, so make sure you use it for more than just the pig snouts).

Using a controller will help you IMMENSELY. I would ask Ross how to hook up an Xbox 360 controller to your PC so you can play without frustration (I assume he often uses controllers to play his PC games on Steam Train) . The controls are much easier to use with a controller rather than a mouse and keyboard, and you'll definitely enjoy the game when you can move around the world better.

Remember to lock on to enemies! If you're going to continue using a mouse and keyboard, it's the Caps Lock button, but if you're going to start using an Xbox 360 controller it's Left Trigger. Also, DODGING IS YOUR BEST FRIEND :D

You can upgrade your weapons with the teeth you collect in your menu! Pause and go to the weapons menu when you have enough teeth to upgrade your weapons. Collect as many teeth as you can and you can upgrade your weapons quicker!

I hope this helps you a bit! I LOOOOVED playing this game, and I hope you see these tips so you can enjoy it as much as I did :D
